  "text": "2 To do this, fix 0 < α < 1 and let A be the diagonal matrix with each diagonal entry equal to An affirmative answer to this question would prove the conjecture. If on the other hand the limit exists for some ϕ but has a value different from α (necessarily larger) then the conjecture would be false. One may try to answer the question by looking for a stronger form of the JuliaCaratheodory theorem in the ball (valid for Schur-Agler mappings). Some results in this direction are obtained in [CITATION_1] , but so far these results are not sufficient to answer the question.",
